	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Most probably, if I had any. But I solved the problem. Here you are how to process, if anyone encounter a similar problem.
<br />
<br />- Open the NES
<br />- Narrow each pin on the connector with some spiky tool, so they can grip the cartridge more
<br />- Facultative, but disabling the CIC by cutting pin #4 help to have a game woriking without have to push it down by 100%
<br />- Cloose your NES
<br />- When playing your game, use a pencil to hold the cartridge as down as possible, and it is enough to have the game working.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
